content:
The CRM Analytics Salesforce Output Connector pushes data from CRM Analytics into a Salesforce org as a Bulk API job. If a portion of the data push fails, use Salesforce Setup and Postman or cURL to troubleshoot.

From Setup in the Salesforce org that initiated the job, enter Bulk Data, select Bulk Data Load Jobs, and copy the Job ID and API version. The job ID prefix is 750 for a single job and 751 for a batch job.

Check the Records Failed column and use the API to investigate the failed records. A row fails because its data couldn't create or update a record in Salesforce due to incorrect date formatting or datatype mismatch.

Create this API URI using your API version and Job ID: /services/data/vXX.X/jobs/ingest/jobID/failedResults/. For example, /services/data/v51.0/jobs/ingest/751B000000JLPLt/failedResults/. Execute the API call in Postman or using cURL.

The end of the raw response has a representation of your failed rows starting with sf__Id and includes an error reason. For example: "ENTITY_IS_DELETED:entity is deleted." To find successful rows, create the URI based on instructions in Get Job Successful Record Results.

For more information on Salesforce Bulk API and Postman, see the Use Bulk API Trailhead module.
title: Troubleshooting Unsuccessful Salesforce Output Connector Run
